The paper presents a data structure for range reporting in high dimensions, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and databases. The paper uses Locality-Sensitive Hashing (LSH), which is a popular technique in information retrieval and machine learning. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also deals with geometric algorithms and data structures, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) as another likely category. The paper also mentions databases and data distribution, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as another possible category. Finally, the paper proposes an algorithm that uses LSH for range reporting, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another possible category.
